    "In the proposed model's bottleneck, we employ the existing PANet [38] architecture alongside CSPNet.",
    "This effectively reduces the computational cost of generating rich feature maps.",
    "Finally, by integrating CSP into the SPP module, CSPPAN's initial calculation set has been augmented at the central position.",
    "Consequently, this enables a more effective incorporation of the CSPNet architecture in both the backbone and bottleneck sections of the network.In this study, we designed to require less FLOPs by adding a hybrid structure to the neural network that is similar to the ViT structure.",
    "This made a positive contribution to reducing both inference and training times."
  ],
